Nnamdi Kanu has said he is holding Governor Nyesom Wike responsible for the killing of Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB members in Obigbo.  The IPOB leader also threatened Wike saying he will be hunted for the rest of his life. He issued the threat on Thursday. Kanu claimed that Wike will be hunted for the rest of his life over the killings of IPOB members and other innocent residents following a clash between the group and security operatives Obigbo, in 2020. In a tweet, the IPOB leader warned that Wike will be hunted by domestic and international legions. He wrote: “Anyone close to @GovWike should tell him that till the last days of his miserable life, he will be HUNTED down for all the atrocities he spearheaded against my people at #Obigbo. “He will be hunted by legions, domestically and internationally. And it will be scorched-earth and fiery.” Members of IPOB had allegedly engaged security operatives, a situation that led to the killing of people in Obigbo area of Rivers State.  Source Nnamdi Kanu has vowed to deal with Rivers state Governor, Nyesom Wike and the Nigerian Army. The leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB said Wike and the Nigerian Army will pay a heavy price over the recent killing by security agents in Oyigbo Local Government Area, Rivers State.… In "News" The leadership of Ohanaeze Ndigbo Youth Council Worldwide says that the group would hold the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Mazi Nnamdi Kanu and the Governor of Rivers State, His Excellency, Nyemson Wike responsible for what it described as “Genocide and Ethnic Cleansing in Obigbo, Rivers State.… In "News" Leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) Nnamdi Kanu called on the Inspector General of Police to investigate the alleged secret abduction, torture, detention, and killing of members of the proscribed group in Special Anti- Robbery Squad (SARS) cells. “The Police SARS in Awkuzu Anambra State and Obigbo in… In "News"